data.name: BBQ Pulled Pork Sandwiches with Coleslaw
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender pulled pork slathered in tangy BBQ sauce, served on a soft bun with a crunchy coleslaw.
detailedCookingInstructions: Season the pork shoulder with salt and pepper, and place it in a roasting pan.
Cover the pan with foil and roast for about 6 hours, or until the pork is tender and easily shredded.
Once cooked, remove the pork from the oven and let it rest for 30 minutes before shredding it with two forks.
In a saucepan, combine the BBQ sauce and shredded pork, and heat until warmed through.
For the coleslaw, combine shredded cabbage, carrots, mayonnaise, apple cider vinegar, and sugar in a bowl. Mix well until all the ingredients are combined.
To serve, pile the pulled pork onto a bun, top with coleslaw, and enjoy!
